---
import BaseLayout from '../components/layout/BaseLayout.astro';
import { SITE } from '../config/site';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About"
  description="About Asavin Wattanajantra and Editorial Intelligence OS."
>
  <div class="container-site py-20">
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <header class="mb-16">
        <p class="t-label mb-6">About</p>
        <h1 class="t-heading mb-6">{SITE.author}</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-[var(--color-ink-secondary)] leading-relaxed">
          {SITE.title}
        </p>
      </header>

      <hr class="divider mb-16" />

      <div class="about-photo mb-16">
        <img src="/Images/asavin.jpg" alt="Asavin Wattanajantra" class="about-img" />
      </div>

      <div class="about-prose">
        <p>
          I'm a content strategist and editorial intelligence practitioner working at the intersection of research, narrative and knowledge systems.
        </p>
        <p>
          My work focuses on helping organisations transform what they already know into connected narratives, reusable frameworks and strategic assets that compound in value over time.
        </p>
        <p>
          The ideas on this site emerged from practical work — most extensively at Sage, where programmes like <a href="/narratives/hidden-hours" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Hidden Hours</a>, <a href="/narratives/customer-stories" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Customer Stories</a> and <a href="/narratives/trusted-ai" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Trusted AI</a> developed into something beyond content campaigns: knowledge systems designed to strengthen with every new cycle of evidence.
        </p>
        <p>
          Editorial Intelligence OS is where I document that work, develop the underlying framework and build the tools that make the discipline repeatable.
        </p>

        <h2>Where this came from</h2>
        <p>
          This isn't theory. It's two decades of content practice, synthesised.
        </p>
        <p>
          I've spent years in content and editorial roles — writing, commissioning, running research programmes, building campaigns. For most of that time, I was operating with an instinct I couldn't fully articulate: that the most valuable thing you could do with a piece of research wasn't publish it, but connect it. Let it pull in the next thing. Build on it rather than starting over.
        </p>
        <p>
          AI changed what was possible. Not the thinking — the thinking was already there — but the speed at which you could structure it, externalise it, make it navigable. This site is what happened when accumulated knowledge met a tool that could help turn it into a system.
        </p>
        <p style="font-style: italic; color: var(--color-ink-tertiary); border-left: 2px solid var(--color-accent); padding-left: 1.25rem;">
          It is not an AI operating system. It is an Editorial Intelligence operating system for the AI era.
        </p>
        <p>
          I built this site in a week. The frameworks and narratives it contains represent years of practical work. That combination — deep knowledge, fast structure — is itself a demonstration of what Editorial Intelligence makes possible.
        </p>

        <h2>What this site is</h2>
        <p>
          This site is a living knowledge platform. Every narrative, framework and article is connected to others through shared signals and themes. The goal is to demonstrate connected thinking — not isolated pages, but a system where each piece makes the others more valuable.
        </p>
        <p>
          It is also a running methodology — not a finished document but something that produces new work as it operates. The frameworks will be refined as new evidence arrives. The narratives will grow stronger as more signals connect to them.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="/practice" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">In practice</a> shows how the frameworks emerged from real work. <a href="/dashboard" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Dashboard OS</a> explains the operating system that powers it. <a href="/experiments" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">Experiments</a> documents active workflows and tools under development.
        </p>

        <h2>Writing portfolio</h2>
        <p>
          My published work — articles, research narratives and editorial projects — is collected on Authory.
        </p>
        <p>
          <a href="https://authory.com/asavin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="text-[var(--color-accent)] no-underline hover:underline">
            authory.com/asavin
          </a>
        </p>

        <h2>Get in touch</h2>
        <p>
          If you're working on similar problems — connecting organisational knowledge, building editorial systems, or thinking about AI and strategic content — I'd like to hear from you.
        </p>

        <div class="contact-links">
          <a href="mailto:asavin@editorialintelligence.co" class="contact-link">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="1" y="3" width="14" height="10" rx="1.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
              <path d="M1 5l7 5 7-5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
            asavin@editorialintelligence.co
          </a>
          <a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/ashwat/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-link">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <rect x="1" y="1" width="14" height="14" rx="2" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25"/>
              <path d="M4 6.5v5M4 4v.5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"/>
              <path d="M7.5 11.5V9a2 2 0 014 0v2.5M7.5 6.5v5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
            linkedin.com/in/ashwat
          </a>
          <a href="https://authory.com/asavin" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer" class="contact-link">
            <svg width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 16 16" fill="none" aria-hidden="true">
              <path d="M3 4h10M3 8h7M3 12h5" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.25" stroke-linecap="round"/>
            </svg>
            authory.com/asavin
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .about-prose p,
  .about-prose h2 {
    margin-bottom: 1.25rem;
  }

  .about-prose p {
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.8;
    color: var(--color-ink-secondary);
  }

  .about-prose h2 {
    font-family: var(--font-serif);
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    font-weight: 400;
    color: var(--color-ink);
    margin-top: 2.5rem;
    letter-spacing: -0.01em;
  }

  .contact-links {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: 0.75rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }

  .contact-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.625rem;
    font-family: var(--font-mono);
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
    color: var(--color-accent);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: opacity 0.15s;
  }

  .contact-link:hover {
    opacity: 0.75;
  }

  .contact-link svg {
    color: var(--color-ink-tertiary);
    flex-shrink: 0;
  }

  .about-photo {
    border-radius: 6px;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  .about-img {
    width: 100%;
    max-width: 480px;
    height: auto;
    display: block;
    border-radius: 6px;
    object-fit: cover;
  }
</style>
